SOUTHERN ILLINOIS UNIVERSITY CARBONDALE.  Southern Illinois University
Carbondale (SIUC) Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering invites
applications for a full-time tenure or tenure-track faculty position in
Environmental, Water Resources or Geotechnical Engineering; applications
will be accepted at all ranks.  The ranks of Professor or Associate
Professor require significant academic or industrial experience, an
outstanding record of ongoing research documented by archive publications,
significant research funding, and teaching experience commensurate with
rank.  Applicants for the rank of Assistant Professor must have a
demonstrated potential for high quality research and teaching with research
documented by publications.  Department provides support and excellent
opportunities for the development of new faculty.=20=20

Candidates are sought with research expertise in novel applications within
civil engineering, including but not limited to:

=20

-Chemical and biological processes in environmental and water resources
systems
-Interfacing related emerging technologies with applications
-Risk assessment
-Computational modeling and analysis of surface and ground water quantity
and quality
-Security and treatment of water supply systems
-Real-time and adaptive infrastructure management
-Response simulation using intelligent agents
-Application of a systems approach to optimization of large scale
environmental, water resources, and geotechnical problems
-Innovative materials development
-Infrastructure health monitoring, design, and rehabilitation
-Progressive failure/collapse
-Dynamic soil-structure interaction under blast, seismic, or impact loading

=20

Applicants must have a Bachelor's degree in Civil or Environmental
Engineering and doctorate by the time of hire in Civil Engineering,
Environmental Engineering or a closely related field in Engineering.
Professional experience is highly desirable. Professional licensure is
desirable and will be required for tenure.=20=20

Applicants must submit a cover letter describing the candidate's
qualifications for the position, a complete vita, a one-page statement of
career goals, and a list of at least three references to:=20

Chair - Faculty Search Committee

Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering

Mail Code 6603

Southern Illinois University Carbondale

1230 Lincoln Drive

Carbondale, IL 62901.=20

Review of applications will begin on March 10, 2006 and will continue until
the position is filled. Preferred starting date is August 16, 2006.  SIUC is
committed to developing a diverse faculty and staff population.  SIUC is an
affirmative action/equal opportunity employer that strives to enhance its
ability to develop a diverse faculty and to increase its potential to serve
a diverse student population.  All applicants are welcomed and encouraged
and will receive consideration.

=20

Regards;

____________________________________________
John W. Nicklow, Ph.D., P.E., P.H.

Associate Professor and Acting Chair

Department of Civil and Environmental Engineering

Southern Illinois University at Carbondale

Carbondale, Illinois 62901-6603
E-mail: nicklow@engr.siu.edu
Phone: (618) 536-2368
Fax: (618) 453-3044
Homepage: http:\\civil.engr.siu.edu\nicklow

=20

=20

=20


